TY  - JOUR
T1  - A comparison of the power of some tests for heteroskedasticity in the general linear model
AU  - Harvey, A.C.
AU  - Phillips, G.D.A.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 2
IS  - 4
SP  - 307
EP  - 316
PY  - 1974
DA  - 1974/12/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(74)90016-5
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407674900165
AB  - An exact parametric test against heteroskedasticity in the general linear model is proposed. Its power is compared with that of the test proposed by Goldfeld and Quandt and with the BLUS test. Under a variety of circumstances all three tests are found to be of compare power. The proposed test is similar to the BLUS test but is based on easily computed recursive residuals and it is believed that the flexibility and computational simplicity of the new test makes it attractive as a practical procedure.
